4 A lot of people have been talking about this place, and when I saw the Groupon it was my key to try it.  I ordered smash fries, 1/3 Sin City burger and a root beer float to go. While I was driving in my car, I was munching on the smash fries. Too much rosemary, not enough salt. Just not good flavor, which left me thinking the burger would be mediocre as well.  When I got to my destination, I unwrapped the burger. It looked super greasy and unappealing, but whoa! Seriously the best burger that I have ever had! It melted in my mouth, which almost seems impossible for a burger, but it did. The bun is soft and fresh. The meat is juicy and full of flavor. Altogether, amazing!   Someone said it's not as good as Five Guys - Wrong! The actual burger is better than In-N-Out (had it for lunch the same day, so it was fresh in my memory), Shack Shake in New York, Five Guys, Grind Burger, Burger Bar, etc.  Pass on the fries. They need to work of those! The root beer float you can make on your own.   Yes it is pricey, but it's gourmet. Totally worth it.
