5 This place is really good!   I mean, you have to have some cojones to open up a burger shop next to In-N-Out burger, right? I mean, that's some stiff competition. But Smashburger is holding their own and they make a tasty burger.   I've eaten here a handful of times but I've only tasted two burgers because they're so good, I always get them. My favorite is the Sin City burger for $5.99. It has Fried egg, applewood smoked bacon, American cheese, grilled onions, haystack onions and smash sauce on an egg bun. The smash sauce tastes like a mixture of yellow mustard and relish. It's a great burger, my only complaint is, like Sin City itself, it's overkill, there's too much going on. I've remedied the problem by eating the bacon, then the haystack onions by themselves, and just leaving the burger, egg, grilled onions and sauce together. It works mighty fine for me.   Their truffle mushroom swiss burger is fantastic too. Of course, as their namesake says, their burgers get their great flavor from being smashed, so the outside is crispy but the inside is juicy (ask for it medium just to make sure).   Honorable mention are their Smash fries (fries coated with olive oil and rosemary), their sweet potato fries and their milkshakes (made with Haagen Daz ice cream).
